By Heron's formula,
\begin{align*}
[\triangle ABC] &= \sqrt{s(s - AB)(s - AC)(s - BC)} \\
&= \sqrt{\frac{3x}{2} \cdot \frac{x}{2} \cdot \frac{x + 3}{2} \cdot \frac{x - 3}{2}} \\
&= \frac{3}{4} x \sqrt{x^2 - 9} \\
&= \frac{3}{4} \cdot \frac{5}{3} \cdot \sqrt{\left( \frac{5}{3} \right)^2 - 9} \\
&= \boxed{\frac{5 \sqrt{7}}{9}}.
\end{align*}

Let $O_1$ and $O_2$ be the centers of the circles with radii 1 and 2, respectively, as shown below.

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,O1,O2;
O1=(0,5);
O2=(0,2);
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
draw(A--B--C--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
