label("$O_2$",O2,N);
label("2",(1,2),N);
label("1",(0.5,5),N);
label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,SW);
label("$C$",C,SE);
[/asy]

Since $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{AC}$ are tangent to the circle with center $O_1,$ we have $AB = AC = 1.$  Let $P$ be the projection of $O_1$ onto $\overline{BC}.$  Then $O_1 P = 1,$ $O_2 P = 2,$ and $BC = 3.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,O1,O2,P;
O1=(0,5);
O2=(0,2);
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
P=(0,0);
draw(A--B--C--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O1,1),linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O2,2),linewidth(0.7));
draw((0,2)--(2,2));
draw((0,5)--(1,5));
draw(O1--P);
draw(O2--P);
draw(rightanglemark(O1,P,B,3.2));
label("$O_1$",O1,N);
label("$O_2$",O2,N);
label("2",(1,2),N);
label("1",(0.5,5),N);
label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,SW);
label("$C$",C,SE);
label("$P$",P,S);
label("$1$",(0.5,2.5),E);
label("$2$",(1,3.5),W);
label("$3$",(0,-1.5),S);
[/asy]

Then by the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $O_1 PB,$ we get
\[OB^2 = O_1 B^2 + O_1 P^2 = 2^2 + 1^2 = 5.\]Then $ABO_2$ is a right triangle, so $\angle O_2 AB = 90^\circ.$  Therefore, $\angle BAC = \angle O_2 AB + \angle O_2 AC = 90^\circ + 90^\circ = 180^\circ,$ so $\triangle ABC$ is a straight line, and its area is $\boxed{0}.$

Let $D$ be the point of tangency of the circle of radius 1 and $\overline{AC},$ and let $E$ be the point of tangency of the circle of radius 2 and $\overline{AB}.$  Let $F$ be the intersection of $\overline{AC}$ and $\overline{BE}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,D,EE,F;
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
D=(0,5);
EE=(-2,0);
F=(0,2);
