label("1",(0.5,5),N);
label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,SW);
label("$C$",C,SE);
[/asy]

Since $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{AC}$ are tangent to the circles, $BD = BE = 2$ and $CD = AD = 3.$  Also, $DE = 1.$

Since $\overline{AB}$ is tangent to the circle of radius 2, $\angle AEB = 90^\circ.$  Then $\triangle AEB$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AE = \sqrt{3}.$  Then $BF = 2 - \sqrt{3}.$

Since $\overline{AC}$ is tangent to the circle of radius 1, $\angle AFD = 90^\circ.$  Also, $\angle AFE = \angle AEB = 60^\circ.$  Therefore, $\triangle AFE$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $AF = \frac{1}{2}.$  Then $FC = \frac{5}{2} - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{3}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,D,EE,F;
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
D=(0,5);
EE=(-2,0);
F=(0,2);
