label("$\frac{1}{2}$", (0,3));
[/asy]

Hence, the area of $\triangle ABC$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot BC \cdot AF = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \left( 2 \left( 2 - \sqrt{3} \right) + \frac{5}{2} - \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{3} \right) \cdot \frac{1}{2} = \boxed{\frac{3}{4} - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{4}}.\]

Let $O_1$ and $O_2$ be the centers of the circles with radii 1 and 2, respectively, and let $P$ be the point of intersection of $\overline{BC}$ and $\overline{O_1O_2}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,O1,O2,P;
O1=(0,5);
O2=(0,2);
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
P=(0,1.6);
draw(A--B--C--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O1,1),linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O2,2),linewidth(0.7));
draw((0,2)--(0,5),linewidth(0.7));
draw((0,1.6)--(0,8),linewidth(0.7));
