Then $AP = AB - BP = \sqrt{(1 - x)^2 + 1} - \frac{3}{4},$ so the area of triangle $ABC$ is
\begin{align*}
[ABC] &= \frac{1}{2} \cdot BC \cdot AP \\
&= \frac{1}{2} \cdot 1 \cdot \left( \sqrt{(1 - x)^2 + 1} - \frac{3}{4} \right) \\
&= \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{2}}{8}}.
\end{align*}

Let $O_1$ and $O_2$ be the centers of the small and large circles, respectively.  Let $D$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $O_1$ to $AB,$ and let $E$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $O_2$ to $AB,$ as shown below.

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,D,EE,O1,O2;
A=(0,8);
B=(-2.8,0);
C=(2.8,0);
O1=(0,5);
O2=(0,2);
D=(0,3);
EE=(0,0);
