Since $\overline{AB}$ is tangent to the circle with center $O_1,$ $OD = 1.$  Since $\overline{AB}$ is tangent to the circle with center $O_2,$ $EB = 2.$  Then $AD = AB - BD = AB - EB = 1,$ so $OD = AD.$  Hence, $\triangle O_1 AD$ is isosceles, and $\angle ADO_1 = \angle DAO_1.$  But $\angle DAO_1 = \angle O_1 AC,$ so
\[\angle ADO_1 = \angle O_1 AC = \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC.\]Similarly, $\angle AEO_2 = \angle CAO_2 = \frac{1}{2} \angle BAC.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.7cm);
pair A,B,C,D,EE,O1,O2;
